Components Explained
1. Firewalls
Why Add This?
Firewalls filter traffic, blocking unauthorized access to the servers.

Firewall 1: Protects the load balancer from malicious requests.
Firewall 2: Secures the application servers from direct user access.
Firewall 3: Protects the database from external access, allowing only requests from application servers.